description: Thanks to an arranged marriage that was designed to make an ailing grandmother happy, newlyweds Rahul and Swati are virtually strangers. Can a four-day honeymoon make a difference when it comes to the couple's feelings about each other?

title: يوم الدين
cast: Rady Gamal, Ahmed Abdelhafiz, Shahira Fahmy, Shehab Ibrahim, Mohamed Abd El Azim, Osama Abdullah, Khaled Raafat, Mohamed Qishta, Shoq Emara, Mahmoud Fares
description: A man cured of leprosy and a young orphan leave their colony for the first time to travel across Egypt, hoping to find the families they lost.

title: Yes or No
cast: Sushar Manaying, Supanart Jittaleela, Arisara Thongborisut, Soranut Yupanun, Inthira Yeunyong
description: Traditional girl Pie is initially uncomfortable with her tomboyish new roommate. But as time goes on, she finds herself increasingly attracted to her.

title: Yes or No 2
cast: Supanart Jittaleela, Sushar Manaying, Nisa Boonsantear, Apittha Khlaiudom, Apapattra Meesang
description: No longer university girls, Kim and Pie face new hurdles in their relationship, including work, new friends and other distractions.

title: Yes or No 2.5
cast: Supanart Jittaleela, Pimpakan Bangchawong, Chansakorn Kittiwattanakorn, Sunanta Yoonniyom
description: Roommates Wine and Pie find their lives turned upside down when two more ladies move in next door, bringing up past heartaches and new attractions.

title: Yoga Hosers
cast: Harley Quinn Smith, Lily-Rose Depp, Johnny Depp, Justin Long, Austin Butler, Tyler Posey, Stan Lee, Jason Mewes, Adam Brody, Haley Joel Osment, Genesis Rodriguez
description: With an all-important high school party at stake, two teen yoga fanatics enlist a man hunter to help fight an army of monsters created by Nazis.

title: You Changed My Life
cast: John Lloyd Cruz, Sarah Geronimo, Rayver Cruz, Dante Rivero, Rowell Santiago, Al Tantay, Irma Adlawan, Bernard Palanca, Matet De Leon, Joross Gamboa
description: Laida and Miggy think they've found perfect happiness with each other, until their burgeoning careers force them into a long-distance relationship.

title: Young Adult
cast: Charlize Theron, Patton Oswalt, Patrick Wilson, Elizabeth Reaser, Jill Eikenberry, Mary Beth Hurt, Collette Wolfe, Richard Bekins, Kate Nowlin
description: When a divorced writer gets a letter from an old boyfriend announcing his wife's had a baby, she returns to her hometown to reconnect with her ex.

title: اشتباك
cast: Nelly Karim, Hany Adel, Tarek Abdel Aziz, Ahmed Malek, Ahmed Dash, Husni Sheta, Aly Eltayeb, Amr El Kady, Mohamed Abd El Azim, Gameel Barsoum, Ashraf Hamdy
description: Amid the tumult following Egyptian President Morsi's ouster, demonstrators from divergent backgrounds are brought together inside a police truck.

title: Zed Plus
cast: Adil Hussain, Mona Singh, K.K. Raina, Sanjay Mishra, Anil Rastogi, Ravi Jhankal, Kulbhushan Kharbanda, Ekavali Khanna, Mukesh Tiwari, Vinod Acharya
description: A philandering small-town mechanic's political ambitions are sparked when the visiting prime minister mistakenly grants him special security clearance.

title: Zinzana
cast: Ali Suliman, Saleh Bakri, Yasa, Ali Al-Jabri, Mansoor Alfeeli, Ahd
description: Recovering alcoholic Talal wakes up inside a small-town police station cell, where he's subject to the mind games of a psychotic sadist.

title: Zodiac
cast: Mark Ruffalo, Jake Gyllenhaal, Robert Downey Jr., Anthony Edwards, Brian Cox, Elias Koteas, Donal Logue, John Carroll Lynch, Dermot Mulroney, Chloë Sevigny
description: A political cartoonist, a crime reporter and a pair of cops investigate San Francisco's infamous Zodiac Killer in this thriller based on a true story.

title: Zubaan
cast: Vicky Kaushal, Sarah-Jane Dias, Raaghav Chanana, Manish Chaudhary, Meghna Malik, Malkeet Rauni, Anita Shabdish, Chittaranjan Tripathy
description: A scrappy but poor boy worms his way into a tycoon's dysfunctional family, while facing his fear of music and the truth about his past.
